            "title": "CARE",
            "content": "<ol><li><strong>Wash at 30°C (85°F) in the washing machine or by hand</strong><br/>Use the delicate cycle if machine washing. Unlike drugstore tights that rip if you breathe on them, these are <strong>built to last</strong>—no drama needed.<br/></li><li><strong>Use regular detergent (no bleach, no fabric softener)</strong><br/>A gentle detergent works best, but don't overthink it. Skip bleach and fabric softener—they damage the sculpting fibers, and these are already <strong>luxuriously soft</strong>.<br/></li><li><strong>Lay flat or hang to dry (NEVER use the dryer)</strong><br/>The dryer is your enemy. Just hang them normally or lay flat. Avoid direct sunlight or the shade may fade.<br/></li><li><strong>Fold carefully and store in your drawer</strong><br/>No weird creases or they'll lose shape. Treat them like your favorite piece—no special museum drawer required, just normal care.<br/></li><li><strong>Replace only when necessary</strong><br/>If the control band stops holding as well or the fabric shows wear, time for a new pair. But relax—these <strong>last WAY longer</strong> than those $15 tights that rip after one wear.<br/></li></ol><p>Pro Tip: Buy 2-3 pairs and rotate them throughout the week so they last <strong>twice as long</strong>.</p>",
